    <div class="full-title with-title-branding">
      <div class="title-branding"><a href="/taxonomy/term/868"><img src="https://www2.bfi.org.uk/sites/bfi.org.uk/files/styles/16x9_small/public/sight-and-sound-logo-280x69.png?itok=AEegRSbk" alt="" /></a></div>
  
  <h1>
          The Greatest Documentaries of All Time poll    
    
      </h1>

  
  
        <div class="copy">
              <div class="intro"><p class="p1"><span class="s1">What are the greatest documentaries ever made? We polled 340 critics, programmers and filmmakers in the search for authoritative answers.</span></p>
</div>
            
      
      
      
          </div>
  </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="block">
      
  <div class="content">
    <div class="small-12 large-12 columns solo">
  
  
  
  </div>


<div class="clear"></div>
  </div>
</div>
      
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Content row -->
  <div id="main-content" class="row layout-box">

          <div id="region-content-left-1" class="large-8 small-12 columns left layout-item layout-item-first">
        <div class="block">
      
  <div class="content">
    <div class="small-12 large-12 columns solo">
  
  
  
  </div>


<div class="clear"></div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="block">
      
  <div class="content">
    

                    <div class="primary box">

                            <h2>The polls</h2>          <ul class="equalise xsmall-block-grid-1 small-block-grid-2 large-block-grid-3 with-bottom-margin">
                          <li>

                                                                    <a class="img " href="/sight-sound-magazine/greatest-docs"><img class="full" src="https://www2.bfi.org.uk/sites/bfi.org.uk/files/styles/16x9_small/public/news/greatest-documentaries-of-all-time-art-001_1000x750.jpg?itok=BPeYJ278" alt="Critics’ 50 Greatest Documentaries of All Time" /></a>
                
                
                                  <p class='h5'><a href="/sight-sound-magazine/greatest-docs">Critics’ 50 Greatest Documentaries of All Time</a></p>
                  <p>The greatest documentaries as nominated by 237 critics, curators and academics.
                    <br /><span class='date'>Friday 1 August 2014</span>                                      </p>
                                  
              </li>
                          <li>

                                                                    <a class="img " href="/sight-sound-magazine/filmmakers-greatest-docs"><img class="full" src="https://www2.bfi.org.uk/sites/bfi.org.uk/files/styles/16x9_small/public/news/man-with-a-movie-camera-1929-002-kino-eye_1000x750.jpg?itok=P4WzqVbn" alt="Filmmakers’ Greatest Documentaries of All Time" /></a>
                
                
                                  <p class='h5'><a href="/sight-sound-magazine/filmmakers-greatest-docs">Filmmakers’ Greatest Documentaries of All Time</a></p>
                  <p>The greatest documentaries ever made, as voted by 103 directors.
                    <br /><span class='date'>Friday 1 August 2014</span>                                      </p>
                                  
              </li>
                          <li>

                                                                    <a class="img " href="http://www.bfi.org.uk/sight-sound-magazine/greatest-docs-full-poll"><img class="full" src="https://www2.bfi.org.uk/sites/bfi.org.uk/files/styles/16x9_small/public/external_link/sight-sound-doc-poll-film-and-tape-carriers-intro-layout_1000x750.jpg?itok=qU7Uyoz_" alt="The Greatest Documentaries of All Time – all the votes" /></a>
                
                
                                  <p class='h5'><a href="http://www.bfi.org.uk/sight-sound-magazine/greatest-docs-full-poll">The Greatest Documentaries of All Time – all the votes</a></p>
                  <p>Browse all the votes and comments in our poll of 340 documentary critics, curators, academics and filmmakers.
                                                          </p>
                                  
              </li>
                      </ul>
          <div class="clear"></div>
        </div>

                        <div class="primary box">

                            <h2>Video</h2>          <ul class="equalise xsmall-block-grid-1 small-block-grid-2 large-block-grid-3 with-bottom-margin">
                          <li>

                                                                    <a class="img " href="/explore-film-tv/sight-sound-magazine/video/dear-john-grierson-postscript-story-film-rough-cut"><img class="full" src="https://www2.bfi.org.uk/sites/bfi.org.uk/files/styles/16x9_small/public/news/dear-john-grierson-2014-001-engineer-entering-train-workshop_1000x750.jpg?itok=yIGldQRA" alt="Dear John Grierson: A Postscript to The Story of Film (rough cut)" /></a>
                
                
                                  <p class='h5'><a href="/explore-film-tv/sight-sound-magazine/video/dear-john-grierson-postscript-story-film-rough-cut">Dear John Grierson: A Postscript to The Story of Film (rough cut)</a></p>
                  <p>All aboard the good train cinephilia, as Mark Cousins conducts us to lesser-visited stations around the documentary globe.
                    <br /><span class='date'>Friday 1 August 2014</span>                                      </p>
                                  
              </li>
                          <li>

                                                                    <a class="img " href="/explore-film-tv/sight-sound-magazine/video/art-nonfiction"><img class="full" src="https://www2.bfi.org.uk/sites/bfi.org.uk/files/styles/16x9_small/public/news/art-of-nonfiction-video-essay_1000x750_1.jpg?itok=5ndPd3JX" alt="Video: the art of nonfiction" /></a>
                
                
                                  <p class='h5'><a href="/explore-film-tv/sight-sound-magazine/video/art-nonfiction">Video: the art of nonfiction</a></p>
                  <p>Robert Greene essays a love letter to the “magical imitation of reality”.
                    <br /><span class='date'>Thursday 7 August 2014</span>                                      </p>
                                  
              </li>
                          <li>

                                                                    <a class="img " href="/explore-film-tv/sight-sound-magazine/video/what-was-documentary-elegy-robert-gardner"><img class="full" src="https://www2.bfi.org.uk/sites/bfi.org.uk/files/styles/16x9_small/public/news/what-was-documentary_1000x750_0.jpg?itok=Cog6CioF" alt="What was documentary? An elegy for Robert Gardner" /></a>
                
                
                                  <p class='h5'><a href="/explore-film-tv/sight-sound-magazine/video/what-was-documentary-elegy-robert-gardner">What was documentary? An elegy for Robert Gardner</a></p>
                  <p>Is it time to put away this mirage of ‘nonfiction’ cinema, asks Kevin B. Lee?
                    <br /><span class='date'>Thursday 28 August 2014</span>                                      </p>
                                  
              </li>
                      </ul>
          <div class="clear"></div>
        </div>

                        <div class="primary box">

                            <h2>Features</h2>          <ul class="equalise xsmall-block-grid-1 small-block-grid-2 large-block-grid-3 with-bottom-margin">
                          <li>

                                                                    <a class="img " href="http://edition.pagesuite-professional.co.uk/launch.aspx?eid=95c7efde-cedb-49bb-aa99-4e938ac21d8a"><img class="full" src="https://www2.bfi.org.uk/sites/bfi.org.uk/files/styles/16x9_small/public/external_link/sight-sound-doc-poll-archive-dossier_1000x750.jpg?itok=q6NI23bG" alt="The 10 Greatest Documentaries – writing from the S&S archives" /></a>
                
                
                                  <p class='h5'><a href="http://edition.pagesuite-professional.co.uk/launch.aspx?eid=95c7efde-cedb-49bb-aa99-4e938ac21d8a">The 10 Greatest Documentaries – writing from the S&S archives</a></p>
                  <p>With a countdown of the top ten films from our 2014 Documentary Poll screening at the BFI Southbank through July and August, we put together this browsable dossier of writings about the films from our archives.
                                                          </p>
                                  
              </li>
                          <li>

                                                                    <a class="img " href="/news-opinion/sight-sound-magazine/reviews-recommendations/top-ten-nonfiction-lessons-those-who-take"><img class="full" src="https://www2.bfi.org.uk/sites/bfi.org.uk/files/styles/16x9_small/public/news/how-to-live-in-the-german-federal-republic-1990-002-two-men-in-fencing-masks_800x600.jpg?itok=AoTR370H" alt="Top ten nonfiction lessons – for those who take the time…" /></a>
                
                
                                  <p class='h5'><a href="/news-opinion/sight-sound-magazine/reviews-recommendations/top-ten-nonfiction-lessons-those-who-take">Top ten nonfiction lessons – for those who take the time…</a></p>
                  <p>Instead of voting in our Documentary Poll, the Austrian Film Museum&#8217;s director Alexander Horwath sent us this proposal for a screening programme…
                    <br /><span class='date'>Wednesday 27 August 2014</span>                                      </p>
                                  
              </li>
                          <li>

                                                                    <a class="img " href="/news-opinion/sight-sound-magazine/comment/obituaries/letter-harun-farocki"><img class="full" src="https://www2.bfi.org.uk/sites/bfi.org.uk/files/styles/16x9_small/public/news/farocki-harun-001-profile-close-up_1000x750.jpg?itok=9C4M9MyG" alt="Letter to Harun Farocki" /></a>
                
                
                                  <p class='h5'><a href="/news-opinion/sight-sound-magazine/comment/obituaries/letter-harun-farocki">Letter to Harun Farocki</a></p>
                  <p>Kevin B. Lee&#8217;s letter to the late filmmaker, written on the occasion of his 70th birthday tribute programme Searching Images at the Nightingale Cinema, Chicago.
                    <br /><span class='date'>Thursday 28 August 2014</span>                                      </p>
                                  
              </li>
                      </ul>
          <div class="clear"></div>
        </div>

